We define strongly cartesian morphisms with respect to a functor `p : ùí≥ ‚•§ ùíÆ`, as in [02XK](https://stacks.math.columbia.edu/tag/02XK). We provide some basic API, and prove some basic properties.

Co-authored-by: Paul Lezeau <paul.lezeau@gmail.com>
